context: The Himalayas were formed around 50 million years ago due to the collision of the Indian tectonic plate with the Eurasian plate. This collision caused the Earth's crust to fold and uplift, creating the world's highest mountain range. The process, known as continental drift, continues today, causing the Himalayas to grow by about 5 millimeters per year.

Yo gases ko emission fossil fuels jasta ki coal, oil, ra natural gas burn garda hunchha. Aru karan haru ma deforestation, industrial processes, ra agricultural activities pani parchan. Deforestation le carbon dioxide absorb garna sakne trees ko quantity kam garchha. Industrial processes le dherai prakar ko pollutants hawa ma chhodchan. Agricultural activities le methane ra nitrous oxide ko emission badhauchhan, jasta ki livestock farming ra chemical fertilizers use garda.
